      Designation: Johann Maus Metal Works AM1.mkV
      <p> 
      Perhaps the finest mecha ever produced in the ULF's history, the newly introduced
      &quot;Ronin&quot; has heretofore been the root of speculation amongst all
      of those outside the SpaceCorps' inner circle.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>
          Initially intended to be in limited production as a replacement for 
          the <a href="rapier.shtm">Rapier</a>, this newest platform has outperformed 
          the specifications originally laid out.&nbsp; This has led to speculation 
          of an increased deployment, perhaps replacing the aging <a href="badger.shtm">Badger</a> 
          and <a href="gekko.shtm">Gekko</a> as well.</p>
      <hr>

</td>
  </tr>
  
  <tr>
    <td valign="top" align="left"> 
      <a href="images/ronin/head.jpg"> 
      <img border="0" src="images/ronin/small/head_small.jpg" align="right" width="100" height="110"> 
      </a> The Ronin's head contains the primary visual optics.&nbsp; With improved
      Low-light, IR, Pan-Spectra, and whisker laser scanning, the Ronin is able
      to operate in all-weather conditions.<br>
      <font color="#C0C0C0">
