  <tr>
    <td valign="top" align="left"><a href="images/ronin/pistol.jpg"><img border="0" src="images/ronin/small/pistol_small.jpg" align="right" width="100" height="105"></a>While the Ronin does carry an
      impressive array of weaponry internally, none of it is considered to be
      it's primary weapon.&nbsp; For that Johann Maus looked to the Browning-Lyfeld
      M375 semi-automatic 133mm pistol.<br>
      <font color="#C0C0C0">
     (click thumbnail to view image)</td>
